trend_summary: From the earliest to latest scenes, the leafy town gradually infills: the commercial core spreads, scattered wooded parcels become housing, and several larger white-roof facilities appear near the river. No extensive sprawl occurs; overall fabric remains low-rise and green, with a slight rise in canopy. Development intensity stays moderate within a predominantly suburban landscape.
notable_changes: Central business district enlarges southwest with new blocks and parking areas.
River-edge industrial area replaced by a larger white-roof complex.
Northern highway corridor sees housing cul-de-sacs added on former woodland.
Southern neighbourhood tree cover thickens, showing municipal greening.
New sports or educational buildings erected east of the town center.
